<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-25T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="607" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.24/159: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-25T12:00:00-06:00">April 25,
                                1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:15 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>73. Honduran Government has ordered 450,000 cartridges for army rifles
                            from the Remington Arms Company to be shipped from New York to Tela
                            consigned Minister of War Government Honduras.</p>
                        <p>Referring to Department’s instruction No. 117, March 20, license for
                            export should be approved.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>